## How to Add Your Media

### SoundCloud Embeds

#### Step 1: Get your track URL
1. Go to your track on SoundCloud
2. Copy the full URL from your browser (e.g., `https://soundcloud.com/nathan-finkel/ambient-set-dec-2025`)

#### Step 2: Find the placeholder in your HTML
Open the file where you want to add the track:
- `projects.html` - For embedded media in project sections
- `music.html` - For the music showcase page

Search for the placeholder text (Cmd/Ctrl + F):
- `REPLACE_WITH_AMBIENT_TRACK` - for ambient/electronic work
- `REPLACE_WITH_GLIA_TRACK` - for Glia performances
- Or find the section you want to update

#### Step 3: Replace the placeholder
Find this part of the code:
```html
src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//soundcloud.com/REPLACE_WITH_AMBIENT_TRACK&color=...
```

Replace `REPLACE_WITH_AMBIENT_TRACK` with your full track URL:
```html
src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//soundcloud.com/nathan-finkel/ambient-set-dec-2025&color=...
```

**Important**: Keep everything else the same - just replace the placeholder text!

#### Step 4: Test it
1. Save the file
2. Refresh your browser (hard refresh: Cmd/Ctrl + Shift + R)
3. The SoundCloud player should now load your track

---

### YouTube/Vimeo Videos

#### Step 1: Get your video embed code or ID

**For YouTube:**
1. Go to your video on YouTube
2. Click "Share" → "Embed"
3. Copy the video ID from the URL (e.g., `dQw4w9WgXcQ` from `youtube.com/watch?v=dQw4w9WgXcQ`)

**For Vimeo:**
1. Go to your video on Vimeo
2. Click "Share"
3. Copy the video ID (e.g., `123456789` from `vimeo.com/123456789`)

#### Step 2: Find the video placeholder
Search for:
```html
<p class="note">Video placeholder — Add
```

Or look for HTML comments like:
```html
<!-- Example:
<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/VIDEO_ID"
-->
```

#### Step 3: Replace with your embed code

**For YouTube:**
```html
<div class="embed">
  <iframe 
    src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/YOUR_VIDEO_ID" 
    frameborder="0" 
    allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" 
    allowfullscreen
    style="width: 100%; height: 315px; border-radius: 12px;">
  </iframe>
</div>
```

**For Vimeo:**
```html
<div class="embed">
  <iframe 
    src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/YOUR_VIDEO_ID" 
    frameborder="0" 
    allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture" 
    allowfullscreen
    style="width: 100%; height: 315px; border-radius: 12px;">
  </iframe>
</div>
```

#### Step 4: Test it
1. Save the file
2. Hard refresh your browser (Cmd/Ctrl + Shift + R)
3. Video should load and be playable

